						<summary>

						<p>This inscription states that the gift of 1000 <hi rend="italic">kuḻi</hi> of land for preparing food offerings to the temples of Mahāvishṇu and Mahādēva. Mentions Iṟalūr in Ayiṟkāḍu and Tiruvindaḷūr in Tiruvindaḷūr nāḍu, a subdivision of Chōḻanāḍu.</p>						

